MC: PropDistMC2-1
PropDistMC2-1

A student conducts a survey for her class project. She asks 22 other students a series of questions about their study habits. She knows from previous research that 0.41 of all students study for 4 or more hours per day. If 0.41 of her own sample study for 4 or more hours per day, what is the probability of observing this sample proportion or greater?
You'll need to correctly distinguish between sample and population when calculating Z for this question. Pick the closest answer.
Z = (phat - p)/sqrt(pq/n). The probability can be found by applying the rule for complements to the probability found in the Z table.
